<item>
            <title>[WFLY-7130] PersistenceProperty specified in @PersistenceContext should be passed to the created EntityManager </title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-7130</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While working on the unit test for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-7075&quot; title=&quot;proposal (Extension): allow checking of mixed persistence context synchronization types to be skipped or to check if unsync context is already joined to JTA TX&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WFLY-7075&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WFLY-7075&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I noticed that PersistenceContext properties are not being passed correctly to the Injected EntityManager, we should fix that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For Example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;@PersistenceContext(type = PersistenceContextType.TRANSACTION, unitName = &quot;mypc&quot;, properties=&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;Unknown macro: {@PersistenceProperty(name=&amp;quot;wildfly.jpa.allowjoinedunsync&amp;quot;, value=&amp;quot;true&amp;quot;)}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
private EntityManager allowjoinedunsyncEm;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is passing an incorrect form of the property values.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
